;; Retrieval gold set — hand-built PL+EN paraphrase queries -> expected nodes.
;; :expect pins stable `source_key`s (repo:path[#anchor]), NOT ULIDs — ULIDs are
;; minted per build, so a fresh code-only ingest re-mints them. load-gold resolves
;; each source_key to the current corpus's id at eval time (absent ones drop).
;;
;; Authored by INTENT, not by echoing current ranking: each :expect is the set of
;; nodes that genuinely answer the question (entity-resolution duplicates — a title
;; that is both a dataset and a benchmark — are both acceptable). A hit is the
;; top-ranked result whose id is in :expect. This scores the product (does a human
;; question reach the right note), so a regression in blend weights or indexing
;; surfaces as a recall/MRR drop. Run: `bb eval:retrieval` (hybrid needs SLAYER_EMBED_*).
;;
;; :lang marks the query language; EN entries over PL-titled nodes are the
;; cross-lingual stress test for the vector lane.

